source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-curried-beef-lettuce-wraps-62b20178fa0f5841f6092fe0
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

In a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, juice from
three lemon wedges, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}. (For 4 servings, use the
juice from six lemon wedges, 2 tsp sugar, and 4 TBSP water.) Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to combine. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside,
tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground beef{10%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @curry powder{1%tbsp}
(you'll use the rest later), salt, and pepper. Cook, breaking meat up into
pieces, until lightly browned and partially cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @chickpeas{13.4%oz} and their liquid and @beef stock concentrate{1}.
Cook until liquid is absorbed and beef is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.
Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Raise heat to high to cook off liquid more quickly.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, remaining curry powder,
and juice from remaining lemon. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at
a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Divide lettuce leaves between #plates{}; fill with filling. Top with pickled cabbage
(draining first) and sauce and serve.